Record.statement_en:
Globalisation is a term that we often hear, especially in discussions about how the world is becoming more interconnected. Globalisation is the process by which countries, economies, and cultures become interconnected and<br />
interdependent through increased communication, trade, and exchange of ideas. It involves the integration of markets, technologies, and policies, leading to a more connected and interlinked world. This means that events or trends in<br />
one part of the world can have significant impact elsewhere.&nbsp;
